    'SecurityLocalGenerateSharedSecret': 'Syntax: long SecurityLocalGenerateSharedSecret(dword curve, byte publicKey[], dword publicKeyLength, byte privateKey[], dword privateKeyLength, byte sharedSecret[], dword* sharedSecretLength)\nDescription: Generates a shared secret between A and B using the Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman (ECDH) protocol. Currently the curves NIST P-256, NIST P-384, NIST P-521, Curve448 and Curve25519 are supported.\nParameters: dword curve The elliptic curve used for shared secret generation. Possible Values: 10 NIST P-256 (also known as secp256r1) 11 NIST P-384 (also known as secp384r1) 12 NIST P-521 (also known',
