    'cclAbstractConsumedPDUGetID': 'Syntax: cclPDUReceiverID cclAbstractConsumedPDUGetID(const char* path);\nDescription: Returns an abstract binding specific consumer side service PDU port ID, which can be used for PDU registration. The returned ID can be used in all consumer side service PDU port functions (not abstract binding specific) but not vice versa. All PDU po\nParameters: path The path to a consumer side service PDU port with abstract binding. See also Communication Object Paths .\nReturns: Return&#160;Values If successful, the function returns a value greater than or equal to 0, which represents the ID of the PDU port. ',
    'cclAbstractCreateAddress': 'Syntax: typedef int32_t cclAddressID; cclAddressID cclAbstractCreateAddress(cclServiceID serviceID, const char* endPointName);\nDescription: Creates an abstract binding specific address, which can be used for dynamically adding service endpoints. All address IDs are invalid at the end of the measurement, i.e. the IDs must be re-determined at the start of each measurement.\nParameters: serviceID The ID of service communication object for which to create an address. endPointName The name of the endpoint for which to create the address. The name must be unique within all endpoints of a service when',
