    'cclAbstractSubscribeEvent': 'Syntax: int32_t cclAbstractSubscribeEvent(cclConsumedEventID consumedEventID);\nDescription: Subscribes a consumer side service event port for an event.\nParameters: consumedEventID The ID of a consumer side service event port with abstract binding (returned by cclAbstractConsumedEventGetID function).\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The event was successfully subscribed. CCL_WRONGSTATE The function may only be called during a running measurement. CCL_INVALIDCONSUMEDEVENTID The consumedEventID parameter does not identify a known consumer side servic',
