    'cclGetUserFilePath': 'Syntax: int32_t cclGetUserFilePath(const char* filename, char* pathBuffer, int32_t pathBufferLength);\nDescription: Gets the absolute path of a user file. In case of execution in a distributed environment the absolute user file path (including filename) on the remote device (e.g. VN8900 ) is returned if the user file was predefined. If the file was not predefined \nParameters: filename A filename potentially containing a path. If the filename is predefined the path is ignored. Otherwise the path is interpreted as relative to the current configuration path in a single PC environment. pathBuffer B',
    'cclIncrementTimerBase': 'Syntax: int32_t cclIncrementTimerBase(int64_t newTimeBaseTicks, int32_t numberOfSteps);\nDescription: Increases the simulation time by newTimeBaseTicks . Use numberOfSteps steps to reach the requested timestamp. For each step, the simulation time is increased. Events that are due are delivered and handlers are called. The function returns immediately\nParameters: newTimeBaseTicks The time span in nanoseconds by which the simulation time should be increased. numberOfSteps The number of steps for the increment of the simulation time.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The time span was set su',
    'cclIsRunningInSlaveMode': 'Syntax: int32_t cclIsRunningInSlaveMode(bool *isSlaveMode);\nDescription: Returns whether the simulation is running with simulated bus with external time source or not. Note The slave mode in CANoe versions prior to 19 has been replaced by the direct configuration of the time source. Select External: Software to get the be\nParameters: isSlaveMode Pointer to Boolean indicating if simulation is running with simulated bus with external time source.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS Always succeeds.',
    'cclIsServiceProvided': 'Syntax: int32_t cclIsServiceProvided(cclProviderID providerID, bool* isProvided);\nDescription: Returns whether a service provider is currently accepting service requests.\nParameters: providerID The ID of a service provider (returned by cclAddProviderByAddress , cclAddProviderByName and cclProviderGetID functions). isProvided This variable returns whether the service is currently provided.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The current state of the provider was successfully determined. CCL_WRONGSTATE The function may only be called during a running measurement. CCL_INVALIDPROVIDERID The pr',
    'cclIsServiceRequested': 'Syntax: int32_t cclIsServiceRequested(cclConsumedServiceID consumedServiceID, bool* isRequested);\nDescription: Checks whether a consumer side service port currently requests the service.\nParameters: consumedServiceID The ID of a consumer side service port (returned by cclConsumedServiceGetID function). isRequested This variable returns whether the service is currently requested.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The current state of the provider side service port was successfully determined. CCL_WRONGSTATE The function may only be called during a running measurement. CCL_INVALIDCONSUMEDS',
    'cclLinChangeSchedtable': 'Syntax: int32_t cclLinChangeSchedtable(int32_t channel, uint32_t tableIndex);\nDescription: Switches from the current schedule table to another one.\nParameters: channel The LIN channel for which the scheduler is to be changed. tableIndex Index of the schedule table to be changed to.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The function call was successful. CCL_WRONGSTATE The function may only be called up during a running measurement or in the PreStartHandler of the measurement. CCL_INVALIDCHANNEL The specified LIN channel is invalid.',
    'cclLinGetChannelNumber': 'Syntax: int32_t cclLinGetChannelNumber(const char* networkName, int32_t* channel);\nDescription: Retrieve the LIN channel number for the given network name.\nParameters: networkName The name of the network, for which a LIN channel should be retrieved. Channel Pointer to a variable, where the function should store the retrieved LIN channel.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The channel was successfully retrieved. CCL_NETWORKNOTDEFINED The CANoe configuration does not contain a LIN network with the given name. CCL_NOTIMPLEMENTED Functionality is not implemented, version 11.0 SP3 or newer is',
    'cclLinGotoSleep': 'Syntax: int32_t cclLinGotoSleep(int32_t channel);\nDescription: Send a goto-sleep master request and set hardware channel into sleep mode.\nParameters: channel The LIN channel that shall be set to sleep mode.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The function was called successfully. CCL_INVALIDCHANNEL The specified LIN channel is invalid.',
    'cclLinGotoSleepInternal': 'Syntax: int32_t cclLinGotoSleepInternal(int32_t channel);\nDescription: Set hardware channel into sleep mode, without sending a goto-sleep master request.\nParameters: channel The LIN channel that shall be set to sleep mode.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The function was called successfully. CCL_INVALIDCHANNEL The specified LIN channel is invalid.',
    'cclLinSendHeader': 'Syntax: int32_t cclLinSendHeader(int32_t channel, uint32_t id);\nDescription: The function sends a LIN header over the specified channel.\nParameters: channel LIN channel on which the LIN header is to be sent. id Identifier of the LIN header to be sent.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values CCL_SUCCESS The function call was successful. CCL_WRONGSTATE The function may only be called up during a running measurement. CCL_INVALIDCHANNEL The specified LIN channel is invalid.',
    'cclLinSetErrorHandler': 'Syntax: typedef enum { &#160;&#160;CCL_LIN_ERROR_CHECKSUM, &#160;&#160;CCL_LIN_ERROR_TRANSMISSION, &#160;&#160;CCL_LIN_ERROR_RECEIVE, &#160;&#160;CCL_LIN_ERROR_SYNC, &#160;&#160;CCL_LIN_ERROR_SLAVETIMEOUT } cclLinErrorType; struct cclLinError { &#160;&#160;i\nDescription: Registration of an event routine for the reception of LIN errors. Registration of the handler may only be carried out in the PreStartHandler. The registered event routines are unregistered automatically at the end of measurement.\nParameters: channel The LIN channel for which the event routine is to be active. identifier LIN id',
