    'cclPDUReceiverGetID': 'Syntax: typedef int32_t cclPDUReceiverID; cclPDUReceiverID cclPDUReceiverGetID(const char* path);\nDescription: Returns a receiver side PDU port ID, which can be used for accessing PDU signal values. All PDU port IDs are invalid at the end of the measurement, i.e. the IDs must be re-determined at the start of each measurement.\nParameters: path The path to a receiver side PDU port. See also Communication Object Paths .\nReturns: Return&#160;Values If successful, the function returns a value greater than or equal to 0, which represents the ID of the PDU receiver port. In the event of an error, the',
    'cclPDUReceiverSignalValueGetID': 'Syntax: cclValueID cclPDUReceiverSignalValueGetID(cclPDUReceiverID pduReceiverID, const char* signal, const char* member, cclValueRepresentation repr);\nDescription: Returns a value ID for a signal in a receiver side PDU port, which can be used for reading signal values. All PDU signal value IDs are invalid at the end of the measurement, i.e. the IDs must be re-determined at the start of each measurement.\nParameters: pduReceiverID The ID of receiver side PDU port for which to access a signal value. signal The name of the signal in the PDU. member A member path for addressing a sub-value of the ',
