    'cclPDUSenderSignalValueGetID': 'Syntax: cclValueID cclPDUSenderSignalValueGetID(cclPDUSenderID pduSenderID, const char* signal, const char* member, cclValueRepresentation repr);\nDescription: Returns a value ID for a signal in a sender side PDU port, which can be used for reading and setting signal values. All PDU signal value IDs are invalid at the end of the measurement, i.e. the IDs must be re-determined at the start of each measuremen\nParameters: pduSenderID The ID of sender side PDU port for which to access a signal value. signal The name of the signal in the PDU. member A member path for addressing a sub-value of the si',
    'cclPrintf': 'Syntax: void cclPrintf(const char* format, ...);\nDescription: Print formatted output to the Write Window of your CANoe . The function uses the printf function of the standard C library of your development environment to format the output. For details about the format string look at the description of printf in \nParameters: format The format string, which controls the output of the text.\nReturns: Return&#160;Values ',
